Vice President Biden met with President Muhammadu Buhari of Nigeria to discuss the importance of the relationship between the United States and Nigeria. They spoke about the challenges and opportunities facing Nigeria and how the two countries can work together to overcome these challenges. They also emphasized the need to root out corruption in order to unlock the full potential of the Nigerian economy and ensure stability. The Vice President expressed U.S. support for Nigeria's efforts to defeat Boko Haram and to invest in development for lasting security, stability, and economic prosperity in northern Nigeria.